description:
Duke professor and acclaimed poet Nathaniel Mackey talks with South African jazz legend Abdullah Ibrahim about his wide-ranging career in music. Ibrahim played with his ensemble Ekaya on Friday, October 16, 2015 at 8:00 p.m. in Baldwin Auditorium. 

A part of an on-going series, Talking Music: Conversations with Scholars, Writes, Archivists, and Artists, co-sponsored by Duke Performances, the Forum for Scholars, and the Duke Africa Initiative.

More info: http://fsp.trinity.duke.edu/projects/talking-music-life-jazz
